entry.title: Chrome draws borders in the wrong place, for percent-height div inside of fixed-height table cell
entry.content:
STR: 1. Load this testcase in Chrome: https://bug1890937.bmoattachments.org/attachment.cgi?id=9396173
EXPECTED RESULTS: * Purple border should not draw outside table/table-cell border. * There shouldn't be any space between the bottom of the cyan box and the purple border.
ACTUAL RESULTS: Chrome draws the purple border outside of the table, and leaves awkward blank space between the cyan box and the bottom purple border.
It looks like Chrome is sizing the table-cell with the border taken into consideration, but then it actually places the cyan box as if there were no border (at the top of the table cell), and then draws the border further out than it should be drawn, or something?
I think WebKit does what Chrome is *trying* to do here, as shown in this screenshot: https://bug1890937.bmoattachments.org/attachment.cgi?id=9396174
(Firefox does something a bit different, honoring the percent height on the div -- which still matches the "expected results" that I describe here, but is possibly an interop issue vs. Chrome/WebKit, tracked in https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1890937 )

entry.content:
